Daniel Thomas `` Dan '' O'Bannon -LRB- September 30 , 1946 -- December 17 , 2009 -RRB- was an American film screenwriter , director , visual effects supervisor , and occasional actor , usually in the science fiction and horror genres .
O'Bannon is best known for having written the screenplay for Alien , adapted from a story he wrote with Ronald Shusett .
He also contributed computer animation to Star Wars , worked on cult classics such as Dark Star , Heavy Metal and Total Recall , and both wrote and directed the horror comedy The Return of the Living Dead .